#stance=stance2
#originalStanceText=At Conception
#originalTopic=when-does-life-begin
The problem with the Roe and Doe cases in 1973 is that the Supreme Court's "solution" to the   abortion   issue was to impose the basically unrestricted right to abortion that existed in New York at the time on the entire country.  The degree of protection afforted to the unborn should be decided by the people of each state, having reasonable discussions like this one, not five justices sitting in Washington D.C. 